<p>I created a TinyMCE plugin and need the listbox items to display html. This is my plugin:</p>  <pre><code>editor.addButton('icons', {   title: 'Foo',   text: 'Foo',   type: 'button',   onclick: function() {     editor.windowManager.open({       title: 'Foo',       width: 300,       height: 200,       body: [{         type: 'listbox',         label: 'Foo',         name: 'foo',         values: [{           title: '&lt;em&gt;Foo&lt;/em&gt;', // &lt;-- Mark save. Render as html.           value: 1         }],       }],     });   } }); </code></pre>  <p>See also the fiddle: <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/allcaps/vqctac3d/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/allcaps/vqctac3d/</a></p>  <p>But the output looks like:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/ubDN2.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/ubDN2.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Expected:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/XFbUC.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/XFbUC.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>How can I mark the list option title save so the contents is rendered as html?</p>